    <note>Shi(4) Xidao [11426] He entered the military service using the yin of his elder brother by a different father, Xizai [8112], but was hated by his younger brother by a different father, Xizheng [11089], who sued over division of property. The court determined to give him a little less of the property and that he change to his original surname, but retain his office, whereas, Xizheng, was dismissed from the civil service and later reinstated with a military office. The only way this makes sense is that Jiyuan [10771], father of Xizai and Xizheng, after the birth of Xizai, took a new wife, who had a son, Xidao, by a previous marriage, and the new wife was the mother of Xizheng. CBD, 1, 434.</note>
